1️⃣ User Entity

Role: Represents a customer (or admin) in the system.

Responsibilities in the process:

Registers and logs in (handled by UserController + security).

Owns a Cart (one-to-one relationship).

Can create Orders (one-to-many relationship).

Makes Payments indirectly (through Orders).

Can later leave reviews (optional).

Key Attributes: id, name, email, password (hashed), role (USER/ADMIN).

Interaction:

Linked to Cart and Order.

Security layer uses User to authenticate and authorize actions.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2️⃣ Product Entity

Role: Represents an item available for purchase.

Responsibilities in the process:

Listed for browsing (ProductController → ProductResponse DTO).

Can be added to Cart (CartItem references Product).

Can be included in OrderItem when a purchase occurs.

Stock quantity is checked/updated during cart addition and order creation.

Key Attributes: id, name, description, price, stockQuantity, category.

Interaction:

Belongs to a Category.

Referenced in CartItem and OrderItem.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3️⃣ Category Entity

Role: Groups products for organization and filtering.

Responsibilities in the process:

Allows users to browse products by category (/products?category=xyz).

Does not change during cart/order/payment but helps filter products.

Key Attributes: id, name, description

Interaction:

One-to-many relationship with Product.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4️⃣ Cart Entity

Role: Temporary shopping basket for a user before checkout.

Responsibilities in the process:

Stores all CartItems added by a user.

Holds a reference to the User who owns the cart.

Calculates totals (via service) before order creation.

Key Attributes: id, userId, createdAt

Interaction:

One-to-many with CartItem.

Linked to User.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5️⃣ CartItem Entity

Role: Represents a single product entry in a cart.

Responsibilities in the process:

Stores product reference + quantity for the cart.

During checkout, CartItems are transformed into OrderItems.

Key Attributes: id, cartId, productId, quantity

Interaction:

Linked to Cart (many-to-one).

References Product for price/availability.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

6️⃣ Order Entity

Role: Represents a completed or pending purchase.

Responsibilities in the process:

Created during checkout from a Cart.

Holds multiple OrderItems.

Tracks order status (PENDING, PAID, SHIPPED, DELIVERED).

Linked to User who placed the order.

Linked to Payment after user pays.

Key Attributes: id, userId, totalAmount, orderDate, status

Interaction:

One-to-many with OrderItem.

One-to-one with Payment.

References User.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

7️⃣ OrderItem Entity

Role: Represents a product within an order.

Responsibilities in the process:

Contains product details at time of purchase (price may differ from current product price).

Helps calculate total order value.

Records quantity purchased.

Key Attributes: id, orderId, productId, quantity, priceAtPurchase

Interaction:

Linked to Order (many-to-one).

References Product.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

8️⃣ Payment Entity

Role: Represents a payment transaction for an order.

Responsibilities in the process:

Tracks payment method (CARD, PAYPAL, etc.) and status (PENDING, SUCCESS, FAILED).

Updates order status when payment succeeds.

Stores transaction details like amount, timestamp, transaction ID.

Key Attributes: id, orderId, amount, paymentMethod, status, transactionId

Interaction:

One-to-one with Order.

Connected indirectly to User via the Order.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔄 End-to-End Process – How Entities Interact

User registers/login → creates User entity, stored in DB.

Browsing products → fetch Product (with Category) → DTOs sent to frontend.

Add to cart → creates/updates Cart + CartItem referencing Product.

Checkout → CartItems → OrderItems → create Order.

Make payment → creates Payment, updates Order status to PAID.

Optional post-processing → Order status progresses (SHIPPED → DELIVERED).